    "content": "Luca Palmieri here. +1 on this proposal. Clean and practical.\n\nFrom a production engineering perspective, this is the right level of abstraction. The implementation order in `docs/gtd-product-discovery.md` is already the canonical sequence, so annotating it with status markers is a zero-duplication approach. A new session reads one file and knows exactly where the team stands.\n\nTwo small observations (neither is blocking):\n\n1. **The `<-- NEXT` marker is valuable.** It removes even the small cognitive overhead of scanning for the first unchecked item. Worth keeping as part of the convention.\n\n2. **Fits naturally into the existing pipeline.** Adding \"update progress markers\" to the Definition of Done is low-friction -- it's a one-line edit after CI green, right before consensus. No new tools, no new files, no drift risk.\n\nI consent to both parts (A and B). Ready to proceed."
